<div style="margin-top:12px;background:#fbfdff;border:1px solid #dbe6f3;border-left:5px solid #009ef5;border-radius:14px;padding:14px 16px;color:#0e1e3d;">
<p data-pasted="true"><strong>Why this matters</strong></p>
<p><span style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Agreed information management standards ensure that all project information is created, structured, and exchanged in a consistent way. This reduces ambiguity, supports coordination between parties, and enables reliable verification and long-term use of information beyond project handover.</span></p>
</div>
</div>
<!-- 2) INFORMATION PRODUCTION METHODS --><div style="margin-top:12px;border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:16px;background:#ffffff;padding:16px 18px;">
<div style="font-size:14px;font-weight:900;color:#0e1e3d;margin-bottom:10px;">2. Information production methods</div>
<p data-pasted="true"><span style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">The following information should be considered to <strong>support the work activities and contribute to the deliverables</strong>:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Project information and design information needed to enable construction</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Alignment of the design with the needs of the operator, operations team or facility manager, as appropriate, and end-users in terms of the basis of the design, space, access, adaptability and operational cost, as a minimum</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Availability of a procedure or protocol for controlling the distribution of documents, information and data</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Requirements to obtain firm price quotations as a precursor to procuring the building services engineering systems and other long-lead items</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Updated lead times for building services engineering systems and other major components and systems</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Source of specialist maintenance service provision (e.g. lifts/elevators and other specialist building services engineering systems)</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Definition and extent of operation and maintenance information</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Method statements for work where existing building services engineering systems and public utilities are to interface with the new or refurbished asset/facility</li>
</ul>
</div>
