<!-- 5) CDE --><div style="margin-top:12px;border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:16px;background:#ffffff;padding:16px 18px;">
<div style="font-size:14px;font-weight:900;color:#0e1e3d;margin-bottom:10px;">5. Common Data Environment (CDE)</div>
<p style="margin:0 0 12px 0;color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;">A Common Data Environment (CDE) shall be used to support the controlled sharing and management of information.</p>
<ul style="margin:0 0 12px 18px;color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;">
<li>All information containers shall have a <strong>unique identifier</strong>.</li>
<li>Information status shall follow defined states (e.g. Work In Progress, Shared, Published).</li>
<li>Access shall be controlled based on role and responsibility.</li>
</ul>
